            content:`A universal 3D animation approach:\n\n1. Plan — thumbnails, reference, timing breakdown\n2. Block in keys — rough extreme positions, no detail\n3. Add breakdowns — halfway poses between keys\n4. Refine in Graph Editor — adjust curves and easing\n5. Add secondary motion — follow-through, overlapping\n6. Polish — frame by frame review, final tweaks\n\nThis works whether you're animating a bouncing ball, a character, a camera, or a logo. The process scales to any complexity.`,
